  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by partially restituting the embezzled funds. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, a 10-year sentence requested by the spectator is disproportionately punitive, especially given the lack of criminal history. A sentence of 8 months is sufficient to address the severity of the crime while providing an opportunity for rehabilitation and continued restitution.",
